1
00:00:06,340 --> 00:00:08,667
I'm back.

2
00:00:08,667 --> 00:00:09,873
- You're back?
- Yeah.

3
00:00:09,873 --> 00:00:12,523
Was it a rough day? Give me your bag. Come on.

4
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:15,097
You did great today.

5
00:00:15,704 --> 00:00:17,461
I'm so tired.

6
00:00:18,352 --> 00:00:19,853
I told you we should come back together.

7
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:21,355
Why did you stay late by yourself?

8
00:00:21,355 --> 00:00:24,662
Because I really want to debut
with you this time.

9
00:00:30,006 --> 00:00:31,323
I'm hungry.

10
00:00:31,323 --> 00:00:32,866
You practiced without eating?

11
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:34,099
Yeah.

12
00:00:34,099 --> 00:00:35,860
Do you want me to order chicken?

13
00:00:38,199 --> 00:00:40,365
Make me ramen.

14
00:00:43,426 --> 00:00:45,727
- You know what that means, right?
- What?

15
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:48,792
If you have ramen here,

16
00:00:48,792 --> 00:00:50,761
you can't just leave.

17
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:55,264
This is my place, so I think you're the one
who might not get to leave.

18
00:00:55,264 --> 00:00:57,257
That's exactly what I was hoping for.

19
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:16,240
You should dry your hair more.

20
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:18,111
I'm sleepy.

21
00:01:48,984 --> 00:01:51,102
What was that?

22
00:02:00,412 --> 00:02:02,122
I'm sleepy.

23
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:05,283
There was something I wanted to do
with you when I got home.

24
00:02:07,044 --> 00:02:08,045
Like this?

25
00:02:08,045 --> 00:02:11,042
No, not that.

26
00:02:11,042 --> 00:02:13,614
Something I wanted to do with you.

27
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:16,659
We can do it tomorrow.

28
00:02:16,659 --> 00:02:18,167
We've got plenty of time,

29
00:02:18,167 --> 00:02:20,407
so just sleep for now.

30
00:02:20,407 --> 00:02:21,805
Okay.

31
00:02:33,904 --> 00:02:34,905
What is this?

32
00:02:34,905 --> 00:02:36,198
[K-pop Star Il Woo Releases Texts and Call Logs
Behind Stalking Allegations]

33
00:02:36,198 --> 00:02:38,492
Il Woo disclosed the texts and calls,

34
00:02:38,492 --> 00:02:40,209
and they're taking legal action.

35
00:02:40,209 --> 00:02:42,204
These texts were fabricated

36
00:02:42,204 --> 00:02:44,831
[Il Woo, why aren't you answering? I miss you]
and bent to fit their agenda.

37
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:46,792
Of course they're desperate.

38
00:02:46,792 --> 00:02:50,128
If Il Woo goes down,
the whole group goes down with him.

39
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:53,715
So what's our plan?

40
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,918
What the hell is Il Woo doing?

41
00:02:55,918 --> 00:02:57,469
Is he out of his mind?

42
00:02:57,469 --> 00:02:59,295
Legal action?

43
00:03:00,889 --> 00:03:03,020
He's completely out of control.

44
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:09,042
Hey, don't worry.

45
00:03:09,042 --> 00:03:11,015
It's not true.

46
00:03:11,886 --> 00:03:15,028
And our company is a major agency.

47
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:17,480
They can handle something like this.

48
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:23,987
Just don't give up like last time.

49
00:03:28,013 --> 00:03:30,743
Are you okay?

50
00:03:32,032 --> 00:03:33,380
Don't worry too much.

51
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:35,461
This will get worked out.

52
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:37,792
Right?

53
00:03:37,792 --> 00:03:39,127
Huh?

54
00:03:39,751 --> 00:03:41,405
Yeah.

55
00:03:43,182 --> 00:03:46,059
Who gave that insider interview?

56
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:47,292
What?

57
00:03:47,292 --> 00:03:50,292
According to a source
close to PNJS's Shin Jae Min,

58
00:03:50,292 --> 00:03:53,817
he had a special relationship
with a key member to secure his debut.

59
00:03:53,817 --> 00:03:55,974
The source said
this kind of practice was wrong,

60
00:03:55,974 --> 00:03:58,271
so they agreed to speak to the reporter.

61
00:03:58,906 --> 00:03:59,990
Who said this?

62
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:02,800
I'll check if someone on our side leaked it
and get the article pulled.

63
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:06,020
I told you to keep the trainees in line.

64
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:09,026
How many times did I tell you
to be careful at times like this?

65
00:04:09,026 --> 00:04:11,376
I put together our response plan.

66
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:13,792
Call Legal.

67
00:04:13,792 --> 00:04:15,193
Yes.

68
00:04:17,393 --> 00:04:20,668
We should put out our own side of the story
and take legal action...

69
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:24,472
Manager Park.

70
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:26,033
Yes.

71
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:28,927
Why do you think I picked Jae Min?

72
00:04:30,486 --> 00:04:32,667
This was as far as he was meant to go.

73
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:34,316
What?

74
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:37,945
Jae Min's role, I mean.

75
00:04:37,945 --> 00:04:41,031
He got us attention through the scandal,

76
00:04:41,031 --> 00:04:44,368
and we got to look like the company

77
00:04:44,368 --> 00:04:47,042
that stood by its trainee.

78
00:04:47,042 --> 00:04:49,792
Then that's all the more reason
to take legal action...

79
00:04:49,792 --> 00:04:53,502
I thought you were sharper than this.

80
00:04:53,502 --> 00:04:58,173
Why waste money on a card we're throwing away?

81
00:04:58,173 --> 00:05:00,820
He did his job, so now he steps aside.

82
00:05:00,820 --> 00:05:04,546
Just tell the press
that we only believed what Jae Min told us.

83
00:05:05,533 --> 00:05:06,640
Still, sir...

84
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:09,017
Still what?

85
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:12,771
I already worked it out with Il Woo's CEO.

86
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:14,375
I mean, let's be honest.

87
00:05:14,375 --> 00:05:17,484
How can we debut someone
caught in a scandal with a male idol?

88
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:19,111
We're not some outlet store.

89
00:05:19,111 --> 00:05:22,155
Why would we sell damaged goods?

90
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:25,188
Wrap that up fast.

91
00:05:37,129 --> 00:05:39,490
Have a seat.

92
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:50,473
Jae Min.

93
00:05:50,473 --> 00:05:52,054
Yes.

94
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:55,633
You've worked hard.

95
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:58,567
The company has done everything it can,

96
00:05:58,567 --> 00:06:00,511
so we'll be terminating your contract.

97
00:06:05,032 --> 00:06:07,859
Don't worry about the penalty fee for this.

98
00:06:27,899 --> 00:06:29,533
<i>The company needs you.</i>

99
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:30,849
<i>We're family.</i>

100
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:33,922
<i>I appreciate you saying that, but...</i>

101
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:37,481
<i>You just have to take responsibility.</i>

102
00:06:37,481 --> 00:06:38,667
[The penalty shall be set at 80 million won]

103
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:40,667
<i>You're an adult.</i>

104
00:06:40,667 --> 00:06:44,646
<i>I was the one who pushed to pick you.</i>

105
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,667
<i>Thank you.</i>

106
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:48,742
<i>We're backing you this hard,</i>

107
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:51,662
<i>so give it everything you've got.</i>

108
00:06:51,662 --> 00:06:53,914
<i>We'll be terminating your contract.</i>

109
00:06:53,914 --> 00:06:56,783
<i>Don't worry about the penalty fee here.</i>

110
00:07:18,897 --> 00:07:20,832
I'm sorry.

111
00:07:21,666 --> 00:07:23,694
You haven't been answering my texts.

112
00:07:23,694 --> 00:07:26,493
Is it that good? Are you that happy?

113
00:07:26,493 --> 00:07:28,446
Look at that glow on your face.

114
00:07:28,446 --> 00:07:30,813
Hyun Jae must be treating you right.

115
00:07:30,813 --> 00:07:32,311
Of course he is.

116
00:07:32,311 --> 00:07:35,779
If you're jealous, date someone too.
Stop living in the practice room.

117
00:07:36,393 --> 00:07:38,700
What makes you think I'm not seeing someone?

118
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:47,554
[CEO Room]

119
00:07:53,106 --> 00:07:54,584
<i>Kim Hyun Jae.</i>

120
00:07:54,584 --> 00:07:57,051
<i>Want to see something funny?</i>

121
00:08:10,853 --> 00:08:12,959
<i>Listen, Hyun Jae.</i>

122
00:08:12,959 --> 00:08:16,046
<i>No one cares about you as much as I do.</i>

123
00:08:16,046 --> 00:08:20,584
<i>So keep doing exactly what I tell you.</i>

124
00:08:20,584 --> 00:08:22,493
<i>Just like you have been.</i>

125
00:08:26,327 --> 00:08:27,883
All our practices got canceled.

126
00:08:27,883 --> 00:08:29,466
Nothing bad is going to happen, right?

127
00:08:29,466 --> 00:08:32,086
I wonder if Jae Min's okay.

128
00:08:32,086 --> 00:08:34,125
We're just taking a break
until things calm down,

129
00:08:34,125 --> 00:08:35,933
so don't worry.

130
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,851
Right. Our company is a major agency.

131
00:08:37,851 --> 00:08:39,927
They'll sort it out.

132
00:08:45,067 --> 00:08:46,401
Hyun Jae.

133
00:08:46,401 --> 00:08:48,436
Let's do that.

134
00:08:54,368 --> 00:08:57,278
Damn it. Failed yet again.

135
00:09:00,541 --> 00:09:01,639
What?

136
00:09:01,639 --> 00:09:03,464
Why are you looking at me like that?

137
00:09:04,066 --> 00:09:05,743
Aren't you going to play?

138
00:09:08,186 --> 00:09:10,050
Did you spend all your money already?

139
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:12,001
Seriously.

140
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:19,884
But when you look at me like that,
how can I say no?

141
00:09:23,379 --> 00:09:24,983
Hurry up.

142
00:09:26,108 --> 00:09:27,453
Yeah.

143
00:09:27,453 --> 00:09:28,944
Okay.

144
00:09:28,944 --> 00:09:31,446
I really want to win that one.

145
00:09:31,446 --> 00:09:33,648
Is there anything you want?

146
00:09:41,693 --> 00:09:43,792
That one's not that cute.

147
00:09:43,792 --> 00:09:45,886
Isn't that one better?

148
00:09:45,886 --> 00:09:47,620
I like this one.

149
00:09:48,793 --> 00:09:50,748
It looks like you.

150
00:09:51,893 --> 00:09:54,220
You think I'm that ugly?

151
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:56,286
You little...

152
00:09:56,286 --> 00:09:59,766
Huh? Hey! Stop it!

153
00:09:59,766 --> 00:10:02,102
Seriously.

154
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,062
You and your stupid strength.

155
00:10:04,062 --> 00:10:06,899
So you hate it?

156
00:10:08,272 --> 00:10:09,782
No.

157
00:10:13,864 --> 00:10:16,825
How about we try to win dolls
that look like us?

158
00:10:16,825 --> 00:10:18,310
Sure.

159
00:10:23,749 --> 00:10:25,750
Why did you press that?

160
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:26,792
No, it won't grab it.

161
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:28,420
Hold on.

162
00:10:44,584 --> 00:10:46,313
That was fun.

163
00:10:46,313 --> 00:10:48,389
Let's come back here again.

164
00:10:51,193 --> 00:10:53,153
Is there something on my face?

165
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:55,420
No. Why?

166
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:57,706
Because you keep staring at me.

167
00:10:57,706 --> 00:10:59,666
That's not it.

168
00:10:59,666 --> 00:11:01,751
It's just...

169
00:11:01,751 --> 00:11:03,247
because you're ugly.

170
00:11:03,247 --> 00:11:05,636
What did you say? Hey!

171
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:54,548
[Korean University]

172
00:11:54,548 --> 00:11:56,633
- I heard he really was a stalker.
- He even fooled the company.

173
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:59,334
- He's basically a criminal.
- I can't believe someone like that goes here.

174
00:11:59,334 --> 00:12:00,375
He has no shame.

175
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:02,492
That's seriously messed up.

176
00:12:08,604 --> 00:12:10,797
I have nowhere to go.

177
00:12:12,357 --> 00:12:14,038
Jae Min.

178
00:12:16,982 --> 00:12:18,762
Khun.

179
00:12:25,199 --> 00:12:28,615
You shouldn't be seen with me.

180
00:12:29,322 --> 00:12:30,735
Why?

181
00:12:31,516 --> 00:12:34,370
If you're with me,
they'll treat you the same way.

182
00:12:40,129 --> 00:12:41,952
It's fine.

183
00:12:51,109 --> 00:12:54,015
I never should've done this from the start.

184
00:13:00,802 --> 00:13:02,572
I'm sorry.

185
00:13:04,201 --> 00:13:06,945
I really wanted to do it with you.

186
00:13:14,582 --> 00:13:16,265
Jae Min.

187
00:13:19,902 --> 00:13:21,873
It's not your fault.

188
00:13:34,342 --> 00:13:36,057
Jae Min!

189
00:13:38,449 --> 00:13:40,311
Come with me.

190
00:13:42,036 --> 00:13:43,630
Where?

191
00:14:03,502 --> 00:14:05,067
Let's go.

192
00:14:12,528 --> 00:14:15,442
I got through it because of you.

193
00:14:15,442 --> 00:14:18,901
It must be hard for you being here.

194
00:14:18,901 --> 00:14:21,477
You did this for me, didn't you?

195
00:14:23,522 --> 00:14:24,823
Hyun Jae.

196
00:14:24,823 --> 00:14:27,326
- How does this make any sense?
- It doesn't.

197
00:14:27,326 --> 00:14:28,869
There's no way.

198
00:14:28,869 --> 00:14:31,959
This is some hidden camera prank, right?

199
00:14:31,959 --> 00:14:33,332
You never used to be like this.

200
00:14:33,332 --> 00:14:35,699
What's really wrong with you?

201
00:14:36,816 --> 00:14:38,912
Just stop already.

